		<div id="comment_body_64709798"><p>I can imagine it.  Not that bicycles <i>need</i> the type of fly-by-wire setups that airplanes have, but it takes a significant amount of tension to move a shifter with a steel wire.  And if you're racing, you'd have to constantly adjust tension and tightness of fittings to make sure that it shifts quickly and cleanly.</p><p>Casually riding?  It would be a convenience but not a huge deal.</p><p>Though bicycles have already been designed with cable routing in mind.  I'm not sure why going with wireless with multiple separate bat<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
